title: For Sale:  Union switch & signal 1911 .45
postcontent: Union Switch & Signal-Model 1911-A1 .45ACP. Issued by the US Army in 1943. This is one of the hardest to find WW2 .45 auto's because very few were made the only company to make fewer was Singer. US&S pistols were made & delivered in 1943 only. Because of the high quality of workmanship in US&S pistols a lot of them were issued to the OSS & the US Navy. The markings on this pistol are correct on the left side above the trigger the ordnance inspectors mark "RCD" in a circle, this is the mark of Lt.Col. Robert C.
